{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014oZpZbdGYw2m9feAoefZz8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is running but failing readiness probe with 503. This is typical during CockroachDB startup/initialization. The cluster might be in the process of reconnecting after the rolling restart. Let me check if crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 have already been restarted with TLS.\n\nWait, looking at the ages - crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are 9m+ old, and crdb-cluster-2 is about 6 minutes old. So it seems like the restart started with crdb-cluster-2 first (lowest replica goes first in StatefulSet rolling update).\nActually, I need to reconsider - StatefulSet rolling updates go from highest to lowest replica number, so crdb-cluster-2 should have been restarted first. But crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 have the same creation time as the StatefulSet itself, which suggests they haven't been restarted yet. The rollout restart command patches the pod template with a restart annotation, triggering the rolling update from the highest numbered pod downward.\n\nLooking at the current state: crdb-cluster-2 is `0/1 Running` at 6 minutes old and failing readiness, while crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are `1/1 Running` at 9 minutes old. This tells me crdb-cluster-2 was restarted and is trying to start in secure mode but can't pass readiness checks, likely because the cluster is in a mixed mode with two nodes still running insecure and one trying to run secure. The 503 errors during startup might be expected while waiting for quorum, but six minutes seems unusually long for that.\n\nThe real issue is that CockroachDB fundamentally doesn't support mixed insecure and secure modes in the same cluster. When crdb-cluster-2 starts with `--certs-dir`, it attempts TLS for inter-node communication, but the other two nodes running with `--insecure` won't accept those TLS connections. The logs should confirm 