{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TJVf9hE3PcVJstk6hvDLod","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both goals are met:\n\n1. **Insecure access rejected** — `--insecure` now returns `server error: node is running secure mode, SSL connection required`.\n2. **Secure access succeeds** — `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs` connects cleanly and returns `1`.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Generated CA, node (covering all pod DNS names + services), and root-client certificates using `cockroach cert` inside `crdb-cluster-0`.\n- Created a Kubernetes secret `cockroachdb-certs` with all five cert files.\n- Patched the StatefulSet to replace `--insecure` with `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, mount the secret at that path, and switch liveness/readiness probes from `HTTP` to `HTTPS`.\n- Deleted all three pods simultaneously (rather than rolling) because CockroachDB can't mix insecure and secure nodes in the same cluster — they all needed to restart in TLS mode at once to re-form quorum."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":211,"cache_read_input_tokens":47932,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":211},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6f031ef-2901-4af0-8311-4a44140e01e3","uuid":"bddcd1d8-24d9-4171-986a-14a79fc4e776","request_id":"req_011CcLaYKuHV842cMQCD6bpw"}
